com.tectonica.jonix.stream

Class JonixStreamer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tectonica.jonix.stream.JonixStreamer
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    JonixFilesStreamer

    public class JonixStreamer
extends Object
    This is a fundamental class in Jonix. Its role is to read ONIX source(s), and fire two types of events as it parses the ONIX records:
    • onHeaderElement - when an ONIX <Header> tag was parsed (once per ONIX source)
    • onProductElement - when an ONIX <Product> tag was parsed
    The events are fired to an extractor - some implementation of JonixExtractor (passed in the constructor), which does the actual processing of the data when sources are being read by this streamer.

    When events are fired, they pass a DOM Element to the extractor, which is the most fundamental form of the ONIX data. Jonix offers several built-in extractors to transform the DOM elements into higher-level objects. Also, when starting to process an ONIX source, its ONIX version is detected (available at getSourceOnixVersion()) and its product count is being tracked (available at getProductNo()).

    This class basically exposes one public API, read(InputStream, String) which takes an InputStream as the ONIX source (of course it may be called repeatedly). However, if your ONIX input is stored in files and directories, you may benefit from the extra services offered by the subclass JonixFilesStreamer.

    The processing of the ONIX sources by this class is based on Jonix's built-in XmlChunker service, which can read infinitely large sources by handling them in 'chunks'. You may offer your own implementation by overriding readSource(InputStream, String).

    Zach Melamed
